{"mode":"Text","textContent":"\ndef when_started1():\n\n    '''\n    This is a bit of code to start off with, it will draw a house.\n    This code is bad. Make it not bad using lessons 1 and 2.\n    You can use functions, variables, and loops to clean it up.\n    Somethings you can add are:\n    - Different house side lengths\n    - Different roof angles\n    - Starting the house at a different point\n    '''\n\n    # Moving to the bottom left hand corner to start drawing\n    drivetrain.set_drive_velocity(100, PERCENT)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(LEFT, 135, DEGREES)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 900, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_to_rotation(0, DEGREES)\n    pen.move(DOWN)\n\n    # Draws a square for the base of the house with 500mm dimensions\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 90, DEGREES)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 90, DEGREES)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 90, DEGREES)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 90, DEGREES)\n\n    # Moving from the bottom left hand corner to the start of the roof\n    pen.move(UP)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500, MM)\n\n    # Draws a symmetric roof at a 45 degree angle\n    pen.move(DOWN)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 45, DEGREES)\n    # Note that: 1.4142 is an estimation for the square root of 2\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500/1.4142, MM)\n    drivetrain.turn_for(RIGHT, 90, DEGREES)\n    drivetrain.drive_for(FORWARD, 500/1.4142, MM)\n    pen.move(UP)\n\n    pass\n\nvr_thread(when_started1())\n\n\n\n","textLanguage":"python","rconfig":[],"slot":0,"platform":"PG","sdkVersion":"","appVersion":"","fileFormat":"1.0.0","icon":"","playground":"ArtCanvas"}